The paper focuses on the security and privacy implications of pre-installed software on Android devices, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper relies on a large dataset and involves analyzing relationships between different stakeholders, which could also place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-categories. The paper also discusses potential harmful behaviors and backdoored access to sensitive data, which could relate to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. Finally, the paper may involve analyzing the code and functionality of pre-installed software, which could place it in the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category.
